<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Saarem on 05-27-2002 02:06 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">You still miss it Naxy...

If you go to a raid where you need a average of X CHers to make it happend. Not X CHers no raid, period.

Then you end with the simple fact:
1. Not enough clerics (today) no raid. Any clerics online need to come regardless of what they planned etc. This leads to a big preassure on them and burn out.
2. Due to burnouts and clerics changing class so will you have to constantly get more clerics (all guilds got clerics as high on wanted, most other classes are not... You would think that after 3 years they would got enough dont you?).
3. Lack of clerics causes people to level up cleric boots only to be able to make raids. They also have to two boot or more on the raids (which in most cases means over all worse performance).
4. Clerics will not get any upgrades because clerics got the strangle hold on raiding and refuse to let go. CH is the strongest spell in game and will with every expansion be even more powerfull as it is the only heal that scales (until tanks can go above 10.5k which with the current cap of 125hp / slot is impossible) with possible exception of slow (also scales but if you want to call it a heal or not I leave up for debate).

If druids on the other hand would recive CH so would that mean less preassure on clerics to be forced to show up to make the raid happend. If you wanted to bring a alt so would it not directly mean a big red flashing no sign. There would also be alot better ground for upgrades because what was hold as the reason to clerics beeing overpowered was removed and we could go long towards druids soloing power which many asked for. Clerics could fit also into other slots as to do the padding healing and assist healing of others, they could throw in nukes, melee etc due to the fact their mana was not needed to be conserved to the perfectness needed to last as long as possible.

There are druids who dont even want CH, and I dont blaim them. Getting CH is a heavy cross to bear and it aint really pure blessing as some thinks. I usually visit most class boards on a regular basis, when a cleric is brought up and the word balanced come in so is the general feeling that clerics are balanced/overpowered due to CH. This is from the regular players who dont get clerics in groups but we got a raiding spot and therefor so are we balanced/over powered. I dont think so, I dont think many on this board think so, but the fact is many do think so. And everything shown so far from VI says they also think so.

Dangrim</TEXTAREA>
